Ad Text:
Transform lives, every single day



Do you want a career that means more? At Anglicare Sydney, we bring the strength, the support and the strategy to make it happen.

We're a well-respected not-for-profit that's been serving society's most vulnerable for more than 160 years. Each year, we achieve life-changing outcomes for more than 40,000 people across NSW. As we continue to grow and evolve, our For Life program is a key initiative supporting consistent, high-quality experiences for residents and staff across our retirement villages.

Your opportunity

12 month Contract - Based in Macquarie Park with travel around Sydney

As our Senior Business Analyst, you will lead the definition, documentation and coordination of onboarding for the For Life program. In this role you will work closely with stakeholders to gather requirements, map processes, and develop role-specific onboarding and induction content and Standard Operating Procedures in partnership with instructional designers.

Reporting to the For Life Program Manager you'll apply strong judgement, systems thinking and stakeholder management skills to navigate complexity, align priorities and deliver clear, practical outputs that support business readiness and change.

With integrity and resilience, you will:

Define role-based onboarding and induction requirements across diverse roles and tailor onboarding by position

Facilitate discussions and workshops to gather, validate and document business requirements

Map and document new onboarding processes and Standard Operating Procedures

Analyse processes, data and artefacts to identify risks, opportunities and improvements

Apply strategic judgement to balance competing stakeholder needs and priorities

Engage extensively with operations, village and project teams, vendors, systems and Digital & Technology teams

Coordinate and drive delivery of documentation, process and onboarding outputs

Develop high-quality documentation including business processes, procedures and flowcharts

Support implementation where required

Contribute to training, coaching and documentation to support change in collaboration with Change Managers

Ensure solutions align with regulatory, compliance, security and organisational standards

Contribute to a strong safety culture in line with WHS and WHSIMS requirements

What you'll bring

You are a senior, people-centred Business Analyst who thrives in complex environments and brings clarity, structure and empathy to stakeholder engagement. You are confident navigating ambiguity and influencing outcomes without formal authority.

You will also need:

7+ years' experience as a Business Analyst delivering business projects

Proven experience leading requirements gathering, process mapping and documentation

Exceptional stakeholder engagement and communication skills across all levels

Strong facilitation skills and confidence leading workshops and discussions

Ability to apply systems thinking, sound judgement and prioritisation

High-quality documentation and writing skills with strong attention to detail

Ability to navigate complex or politically sensitive environments with diplomacy

Experience contributing to business cases, discovery phases and solution design

Demonstrated ability to work independently and collaboratively in project teams

Ideally, you will also have:

Experience in aged care, community services, hospitality or customer service environments

Experience supporting end-to-end implementations including testing, training and transition

Why Anglicare?

We provide meaningful opportunities and choice - for the individuals and communities we support and the dedicated people who make it happen.

At Anglicare, you'll be part of a purpose-driven organisation where your work has real impact. You'll enjoy flexibility, professional trust and the opportunity to contribute to initiatives that strengthen communities and improve lives.

Some of the benefits you will enjoy include:

Salary packaging to increase your take-home pay

Hybrid work flexibility

Meaningful, organisation-wide impact

Ongoing professional development opportunities

Discounts with 400+ retailers

Employee Assistance Program and Fitness Passport for you and your family

Are you ready for a career that means more?

To apply, please click the 'Apply' button. All applicants will receive a response.

Anglicare is as wonderfully diverse as the customers and communities we support. While guided by our Christian values, we welcome people of all backgrounds who share our commitment to serving others. We strongly encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, and people of all ages, genders, abilities and cultural backgrounds.

Disclaimer: We do not accept unsolicited agency resumes and are not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.

Please note: Our Talent Acquisition team will be taking a well-deserved break from 25 December 2025 and will return on Monday, 5 January 2026. We look forward to reviewing your application upon our return.

Wishing you a safe, restful, and joyful Festive Season.

Apply your Business Analyst expertise within the property industry (this is not an IT role).

Bring proven experience in property, real estate, or asset management analysis.

Must have strong SQL experience and be based in Brisbane or Melbourne CBD.


Who we’re looking for?


Solid experience and understanding of the property industry.

Experience with writing SQL queries.

Degree qualification in accounting and/ or Business-related disciplines or qualification in Business Analysis.

Understanding of Trust Accounting / Real Estate Legislation.

Experience with Management Reporting International (MRI).


The role
We’re seeking a Senior Property Business Analyst to provide expert support to our Business Solutions and Asset Management Services (AMS) teams. You’ll play a key role in managing projects, driving system and process improvements, and supporting change management and client transitions.

Key Responsibilities

Act as an escalation point for complex accounting, system, or user queries.

Partner with technical and business teams to enhance systems and processes.

Identify and implement innovative solutions to strengthen accounting and management services.

Participate in testing and implementation of system fixes, developments, and enhancements.

Proactively respond to changing client needs and identify improvement opportunities.

Manage and support client transitions and mobilisations as required.


About Knight Frank
Knight Frank Australia is part of the world’s largest privately owned property consultancy. We specialise in transactional and advisory services, covering the acquisition, sale, leasing, and management of commercial properties from office buildings and retail spaces to industrial assets.

What’s in it for you?

Flexible leave options – Enjoy two additional weeks of leave, two wellness days each year and the day off on your birthday!

Career growth & recognition – Access to mentorship, leadership programs, and ongoing development & recognition.

Lifestyle perks – Enjoy discounts and rewards through our employee reward platform, The Vault.

Inclusive & community-focused culture – Proud winners of Property Council of Australia Award for Innovation & Excellence Award for Diversity, Equity & Inclusion!

Innovative technology & tools – Work with cutting-edge property platforms and tools.


We value diversity
Different perspectives make us stronger. We welcome people of all genders, cultures, abilities, and experiences.

Important to know

You must have valid Australian working rights to be considered.

A police check is required for successful candidates.

We use AI tools to assist with hiring, but people make the final decisions.

We are currently NOT accepting candidates via an agency, we have PSA’s in place.

About Proa Energy

Proa is heavily investing in expanding its energy management platform, delivering cutting-edge solutions for utility-scale renewable energy assets in Australia and around the world. Our multidisciplinary team of engineers, meteorologists, physicists, and IT specialists is rapidly expanding. We're currently seeking a Data Analytics Manager to lead our data scientists and analysts in designing and building advanced analytics solutions that drive the optimal operation of renewable energy assets.




About the Role

As the Data Analytics Manager, you will sit on the management team, reporting directly to the Managing Director, and lead the Data Analytics Team in delivering actionable insights and innovative solutions for utility-scale renewable assets. You will coordinate analytics activities across advanced modelling, software development, operations, and client management, ensuring that new products and R&D projects are deployed efficiently and at high quality. This is a unique opportunity to influence the future of energy management by building and deploying advanced analytics systems (forecasting, dispatch, bidding, data cleaning, ML, etc), supporting clients in optimizing their renewable energy assets, and engaging in “blue-sky” thinking about new products and solutions.




Key Responsibilities

Team Leadership – Manage a group of 8–10 data scientists and analysts, fostering a collaborative environment and delivering deep insights from the data generated by utility-scale renewable assets.

Expert Technical Advice – Guide R&D data science projects, brainstorming technical solutions and contributing to new product development.

Operational Analytics – Supervise and optimise the development, deployment, and monitoring processes of systems running operationally 24x7 for critical infrastructure.

Cross-team coordination – Work closely with product development, software, operations, and client management teams to ensure analytics solutions are integrated and deployed on time and to a high standard.

Regulatory Compliance – Understand market operator regulations and integrate them correctly into Proa’s systems.

Advanced modelling support – Develop and oversee advanced models in optimisation, forecasting, dispatch, data quality filtering, etc. for wide a variety of large scale renewable energy projects (solar, wind, batteries, hybrids, etc.).

System Architecture, Operation and Maintenance – Lead the architecture, operation and maintenance of  Proa’s analytics systems, ensuring processes remain robust, reliable, and scalable.




Skills and Experience

7+ years of experience leading technical teams.

Strong background in data science, algorithm design, machine learning, and physical science.

Experience working with cloud data environments, preferably Azure.

Proficiency in Python and MATLAB, or similar tools.

Strong problem-solving abilities and experience in software architecture and system design.

Excellent communication skills and the ability to lead, mentor, and motivate a technical team..




Desirable Skills

Knowledge of Australian energy regulations, particularly AEMO and NER rules.

Experience building optimisation systems for BESS and hybrid operations.

Experience running real-time operations for renewable energy plants.

On-site asset management and O&M operations experience at renewable energy plants.

Experience with advanced analytics, predictive modeling, or operational optimization in energy systems.




What We Offer

Competitive salary and benefits package.

Career growth and leadership development opportunities.

A collaborative, inclusive, and supportive work environment.

Flexible hybrid work arrangements.




Diversity and Inclusion

Proa Energy is proud to be a Work180 Endorsed Employer, dedicated to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace. We support work-life balance and encourage applications from individuals of all backgrounds, including women, culturally diverse candidates, and people with disabilities.




How to Apply

If you’re passionate about leading innovative software teams and contributing to the renewable energy sector, please send your resume and cover letter to careers@proa.energy with the subject “Data Analytics Manager Application.”

Applications open until the end of January 2026

Applicants must have legal rights to work in Australia.

DMC is thrilled to be partnering with an award-winning, consumer-driven professional services firm in their search for a Senior Commercial Analyst to join their team. 
  
This is a newly-created role where you will be partnering with a range of functions including, Marketing, Sales and Partnerships. This is a high-impact opportunity for a commercially minded analyst who loves turning data into insight, insight into action, and action into growth. You’ll influence strategy across multiple channels and work closely with senior stakeholders to drive performance and ROI.

What You’ll Be Doing:

Performance & Insights

Build and own dashboards across marketing, sales, and partner channels
Analyse KPIs to uncover trends, risks, and growth opportunities
Deliver clear, actionable insights to senior leaders
Deep-dive into campaign, channel, and partner performance
Growth & Commercial Strategy

Partner with Marketing, Sales, and Partnerships to optimise results
Advise on audience targeting, channel mix, and go-to-market strategy
Track competitor and market trends to inform commercial decisions
Forecasting & Financial Analytics

Develop forecasting models across pipelines and revenue streams
Track budgets, performance, and ROI across campaigns and partnerships
Collaborate with Finance and business leaders on planning and resourcing
Stakeholder Engagement

Translate complex data into simple, compelling narratives
Influence decision-making and champion a data-driven culture
Experience / Skills we are looking for:
Prior Commercial Finance / Business Partnering experience - working with non-finance business units
Strong dashboarding and data visualisation skills (Power BI, Tableau or similar)
Commercial mindset with the ability to link insights to revenue and growth
Experience with forecasting, budgeting, and financial modelling
Confident communicator who can influence senior stakeholders
Proactive, curious, and outcomes-focused
�� Why This Role?
Newly created role with genuine influence
Broad exposure across growth, marketing, sales, and partnerships
Hybrid working with a central Sydney CBD location
High-performing, collaborative environment
Clear opportunity for progression and impact
